Concurrency Issues

Double booking :

1. Optimistic Locking


Optimistic locking with version or timestamp
Better to use version as clocks may not be relaible and in sync


Optimisitc Locking : Let users see the value until someone commits
Onc users commits it will increase the version number

Now other tranactions when trying to update will have version less than new version , so fail.


UPDATE property
SET status='RESERVED',
    version=version+1
WHERE property_id=123
  AND version=5
  AND status='AVAILABLE';


Use when Conflcits are rare




2. Pessimistic Locking - Lock the records.



Redis Distributed Locking


If Key is already in DB , someone already locked.
NX = "Only set the key if it does NOT already exist"


Example (Redis Lock)
SET lock:property:123 buyerA NX EX 30

This means:

SET → create a key
NX → only if key does NOT exist
EX 30 → expire in 30 seconds



Redis is external system:

Network partition
Redis restart
Master failover



During these:

Lock might be lost
Or incorrectly assumed released
Leads to race conditions


Added operational complexity


So max prefer optimistic locking


